com.sudoplay.axion.mapper

Class NBTObjectMapperRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sudoplay.axion.mapper.NBTObjectMapperRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class NBTObjectMapperRegistry
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    The NBTObjectMapperRegistry is responsible for storing the object type to NBTObjectMapper relationship and providing a lookup method to retrieve the mapper from its type.
    Author:
    Jason Taylor

        protected NBTObjectMapperRegistry(NBTObjectMapperRegistry toCopy)
        Creates a new NBTObjectMapper by duplicating the registry given.

        Note that this duplicates the backing map, but doesn't actually duplicate the mappers.

      • register

        public <T extends Tag,O> void register(java.lang.Class<O> type,
                              NBTObjectMapper<T,O> mapper)
              throws AxionMapperRegistrationException
        Register a new NBTObjectMapper for the type given.

        If a mapper has already been registered for the type given, an exception is thrown.

        Parameters:
        type - the class of the object to map
        mapper - the NBTObjectMapper to register
        Throws:
        AxionMapperRegistrationException
